/*! \page qlxl_install QuantLibXL Installation

This document explains how to install QuantLibXL.  32- and 64-bit XLLs are
provided.

Download 
<a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/quantlib/files/reposit/1.7/QuantLibXL-1.7.0-bin.zip">QuantLibXL-1.7.0-bin.zip</a>.

Copy the zip file to your hard drive and uncompress it.

\section qlxl_install_usage Usage

To use QuantLibXL:
\li Start Excel
\li Load the addin.
\verbatim
xll\QuantLibXL-vc90-mt-s-1_7_0.xll
\endverbatim
\li Load an example workbook e.g:
\verbatim
Workbooks\EquityOption.xlsx
\endverbatim
\li Hit <tt>Ctrl-Alt-F9</tt> to force a full recalculation

\section qlxl_install_demo1 DOS Batch Files

Alternatively you can use the DOS batch files which are provided to initialize the environment:

\verbatim
Workbooks\EquityOption.bat
Workbooks\BermudanSwaption.bat
\endverbatim

Each batch file should:
\li Start up a new instance of Excel
\li Load the XLL
\li Load the relevant example workbook

A couple of keyboard shortcuts are provided:

\li <b>Ctrl-Shift-E</b>: If a QuantLibXL function fails and returns #NUM, highlight the relevant cell and use this shortcut to display the error message.
\li <b>Ctrl-Shift-X</b>: Close all workbooks without saving them and exit Excel.

\section qlxl_install_demo2 GBP Market Demo

Invoke the following DOS batch file:

\verbatim
Workbooks\BermudanSwaptions\init.bat
\endverbatim

This batch file should:
\li Start up a new instance of Excel
\li Load the XLL
\li Load example workbook GBP_Market_And_Trades.xlsx which includes a GBP
market environment (extracted from the Excel VBA Framework application), an
interest rate swap, and a bermudan swaption.

Hit <tt>Ctrl-Shift-C</tt> to recalculate.  Hit <tt>Ctrl-Shift-X</tt> to exit the demo.

\section qlxl_install_support Support

For further help, please use the mailing list: https://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/quantlib-users

*/

